        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:57AM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 456 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Manderson, which is 15 miles southeast of Basin, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Hyattville around 510 AM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
